{
  "texts": [
    "By Persistence, if φ is true anywhere in M, then it is true at the minimum.",
    "But then φ must be true everywhere, for if M, x ⊮ φ, then by Refinability, there is an x ′ ⊑ x with M, x ′ ⊩ ¬φ, which contradicts the fact that φ is true at the minimum.",
    "(From the topological perspective of Remark 2.15, the point is that in a poset ⟨S, ⊑⟩ with a minimum element, the only regular open sets in O(S, ⊑) are S and ∅.",
    ")What we want to allow is a distinguished minimum ⊥ that does not lead to Fact 4.18.Definition 4.19 (Extended Possibility Frames and Models).",
    "An extended possibility frame is a tuple E = ⟨S, ⊑, ⊥, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ where: ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is a poset with minimum ⊥; R i is a binary relation on S such that R i (⊥) = {⊥} and xR i ⊥ for all x ∈ S; P is a subset of ℘(S) such that ⊥ ∈ P; and the structure E -= ⟨S -, ⊑ -, {R i -} i∈I, P -⟩ defined as follows is a possibility frame as in Definition 2.21:1."
  ]
}